name: Hi
description:
Connections make us stronger, but we are easily distracted. 
It's easy to say hi. Don't forget to connect.
----
Built solely from repeating patterns of 5x5 pixel blocks that form the word "HI".
 ---- 
Viewing guide: 
Look. Look closer. See. 
Turn around until you see someone else. 
Say "hi". 
If you are alone, shout "HI! HELLO?". 
You might make a new friend.

name: Crystal Growth
description:
Crystalline visuals synced to music.
// // Sound on // // WARNING: This video may trigger seizures for people with photosensitive epilepsy.

A visual representation of a large prime number.
- - - - -
Used in cryptography and digital security, primes make much of our modern lives possible - If you're reading this, you're making use of prime numbers. Thank you primes. You weirdly unpredictable beasts.
- - - - - 
Some years ago I had some free CPU cycles, decided to contribute some time to the PrimeGrid project and, over the course of a few months, I discovered/proved a few new prime numbers.
- - - - -
This piece contains the full decimal representation of the large prime you see in the title, inserted into the data stream of a PNG file and manipulated to form a valid image file.

name: They cast me in stone, imagine my relief.
description:
They cast me in stone, imagine my relief.

But too late, there's no escape now.

A crowd too thick, of convictions too strong. 

I cannot walk through them, nor think to breathe.

I am become victim to this modernity, this torturous capital.

Condemned to death, yet compelled to live.

I'll see you in time, great leveller.

Oh, hello entropy.

name: Void Scream
description:
Scream into the void.
And may the void scream back.

Laugh upon a disaster.
The news, a broken back.

My soul rends, as thoughts bend.
A smile forgives, as a child forgets.

Look back, learn.
Lean back, yearn.

Learn from the echoes, 
or follow the pack.

Scream into the void,
and the void may scream back.

name: Computer! Explain yourself!! What is this scene?!!
For you.
description:
/ For you.
//
//
/
/
 What was it like,
 /before the Earth lost it's ice?
/ Are those pictures you showed me the truth?
//
/ Were the bears really white,
/ and did the penguins sound quite
/ like the funny impression that you do?
//
/ Well now, if truth be told,
/ and it certainly should,
/ we've fucked up this planet,
/ for you.
//
/ Through inaction, complacency,
/ corruption, and greed,
/ we've thoroughly decimated it,
/ for you.
//
/ So I'm sorry dear daughter,
/ dear son, dear child of mine,
/ for the future you inherit is grim.
//
/ And there's blood on our hands,
/ because we kept calm and carried on,
/ rather than face the reality of this collective sin.
//
/ So, the Earth's not what it was,
/ and we'll let children die at sea,
/ or put them in cages and try to forget
/ that we'd rather murder and oppress those that object,
/ lest we open our eyes, own up, and see...
//
/ But, in short, yes, the bears were real.
/ And penguins sounded funny, it's true.
/ And I'm so sorry we couldn't,
/ with all the time and the promise,
/ have left some more life,
/ for you.
//
/ [amusing penguin noise]
//
//
/
/
